# Tasty — Design-System-Integrated Styling System

Package: `@tenphi/tasty` — a styling system and DSL for concise, state-aware UI styling with design system integration.

## Key Features

- Declarative, state-aware CSS-in-JS styling
- Design token integration (colors, units, typography)
- Sub-element styling via data attributes
- Advanced state mapping (media, container, root, supports queries)
- Zero-runtime mode via Babel plugin
- Plugin system (OKHSL color support, etc.)
- React hooks for programmatic style injection

## Project Structure

```
src/
  index.ts              # Main entry point (runtime exports)
  tasty.tsx              # Core tasty() factory
  config.ts             # Configuration system
  types.ts              # Core TypeScript types
  debug.ts              # Debug utilities
  static/               # tastyStatic() — build-time styles
    index.ts
    tastyStatic.ts
    types.ts
  zero/                 # Zero-runtime extraction & Babel plugin
    index.ts            # Programmatic API
    babel.ts            # Babel plugin
    next.ts             # Next.js wrapper
    extractor.ts        # Style extraction
    css-writer.ts       # CSS file writer
  hooks/                # React hooks (useStyles, useGlobalStyles, etc.)
  injector/             # Runtime style injection
  pipeline/             # Style rendering pipeline
  parser/               # Style value parser & tokenizer
  styles/               # Style handlers & definitions
  chunks/               # Style chunking system
  states/               # Predefined states
  plugins/              # Plugin system (okhsl, etc.)
  keyframes/            # Keyframes support
  properties/           # CSS @property support
  utils/                # Shared utilities
```

